Text.Value: Oh yay!
That's a shame. You'd like him.
Not really.
Oh. Well. Perhaps some of his exceptional weaponry might change your mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: surprised that ANYONE could not worship Gyldro

Text.Value: Met him once - grumpy fella.
Who's Gyldro?
Do you know him?
You look like you know how to use a spear. Buy a spear, whaddya say? Huh?
Come back soon. And if you see Gyldro tell him... tell him everything's under control.
He doesn't like to be disturbed when he's in the zone, see.
Show me your wares please.
He's just serious about his work.
You don't know Gyldro? Gyldro Angleiron? The smith? Really?
One of those stoic types, are ya? Well, I'm sure Gyldro's got something cooked up that even you can use.
Good to know. Bye then.
There's nothing menial about serving Gyldro Angleiron.
I'd check up on your boss if I were you - he's having a bit of a rough time.
You were expecting Gyldro Angleiron? The smith?
But I wouldn't bother him if I were you - he doesn't like to be disturbed when he's in the zone.
Yuh-huh! I get to talk to people all day and work for the best damn smith in all of Rivington - Gyldro Angleiron.
Oh. All right! Yep! I just gotta find a way to bother him - heh - without... actually bothering him...
Grumpy fella, isn't he?
I could not care less.
Yes! That's him!
Back again! Wanna dagger? Or a bow? Need more arrows? Need a spear?
Are you the one that sells the smith's weapons?
I just came to shop, if I'm honest.
You should be happier to see one of your kin. We're very thin in these parts.
Ahem. I'm a customer. You should be delighted to see me.
Aww we were just getting to know each other... well. Byeee!
Not for you to worry about in any case - you're a customer. Is there anything I can do for you?
Is there anything else I can do for you?
And no obituary in the Gazette? Impossible.
I'd pick a different dream if I were you. Your boss didn't seem the giving sort to me.
Scalefriend! Hiiiiiii! Want a blade? Or a bow? Or a dagger?
Hiiiiiiiii! Want a blade? Or a bow? Or a dagger?
Leave.
D'you know he's won Best Smith in Rivington seven years in a row?
Leave.
Leave.
And AND he says that if I move enough stock, I might even get to have a go on the anvil!
Wait come back! I'm sorry if I came on too strong!
So you want to be a smith?
Quite the little arse-licker aren't you?
Sort of. Creepy, isn't he?
A rather menial job you've landed, fledgling. What path has brought you to such service as this?
How can I help you?
Oh gods - don't tell him I said that will you? I really love my job! Promise!
It's Gyldro Angleiron for gods' sakes! If you knew how good he was, trust me, you'd feel exactly the same way.
I mean - I love what I do, don't get me wrong, but actually doing something with my hands, and all that fire...
What? Don't joke about that. He'll come back, he always does. He's probably just gone to get more coal for the forge, or visit one of the ore mines...
He's not creepy, he's dedicated.
What can I do for you?
Gyldro? Oh... a customer. Sorry.

Text.Value: You don't know him like I do. The way he works the smelter, the tongs, the double-faced sledgehammer...
